cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.NA, cs.SY 

The paper deals with fitting parametric curves on the Grassmann manifold for the purpose of intrinsic parametric regression, which is a problem commonly encountered in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization and control theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of Riemannian manifolds and geometric concepts indicates that it could be classified under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
